UPDATE user
SET name = 'New Name'
WHERE user_id = 123;

No Index 
    Check every row and update

Btree Index
    Random access write hence take sometime

LSM tree
    append to WAL
    update in-memory in SSTable
    SSTable is flushed to disk in sometime

    Read
      Read from in-memory, if not
      Check in SSTable file on disk, return from latest file 

    Async compaction 
      merge SSTables on Disk and keep single merged update copy.

    uses bloom filters for faster look up
